# -*- encoding: utf-8 -*-
# Arc: Other | Scene: TheWarIsWon
# Source: C:\Program Files (x86)\Steam\steamapps\common\The Survival of Sarah Rose\game\script.rpy

translate ru strings:

    old "Sarah awakes the next day in her bed. It was already very bright outside; she wondered how long she had slept."
    new "Sarah awakes the next day in her bed. It was already very bright outside; she wondered how long she had slept."

    old "Memories of the day before come back to her."
    new "Memories of the day before come back to her."

    old "The battle."
    new "The battle."

    old "Her and Varga, in the bed..."
    new "Her and Varga, in the bed..."

    old "Sarah recalled Marion and the audacity of his proposal."
    new "Sarah recalled Marion and the audacity of his proposal."

    old "Sarah recalled letting her brother, Varga and Marion to themselves. They had earned their celebration."
    new "Sarah recalled letting her brother, Varga and Marion to themselves. They had earned their celebration."

    old "She rubbed her temples, trying to physically drive out the memories and focus on the day."
    new "She rubbed her temples, trying to physically drive out the memories and focus on the day."

    old "Sarah got out of bed and began to dress herself."
    new "Sarah got out of bed and began to dress herself."

    old "She wondered in what state she would find her brother."
    new "She wondered in what state she would find her brother."

    old "After wandering the castle for some time, she followed echoes of muted sounds, the embers of a celebration."
    new "After wandering the castle for some time, she followed echoes of muted sounds, the embers of a celebration."

    old "She came upon Thomas in the great hall, where he sat on the steps up to the throne, a last few soldiers still lingering around."
    new "She came upon Thomas in the great hall, where he sat on the steps up to the throne, a last few soldiers still lingering around."

    old "If their behavior hadn't been enough to let Sarah know they were drunk, the smell would have settled it."
    new "If their behavior hadn't been enough to let Sarah know they were drunk, the smell would have settled it."

    old "It surprised her how young many of the soldiers were, barely much older than Thomas. Children really, she thought."
    new "It surprised her how young many of the soldiers were, barely much older than Thomas. Children really, she thought."

    old "As she came closer, she cleared her throat, gathering their attention."
    new "As she came closer, she cleared her throat, gathering their attention."

    old "I think the celebrations have come to an end. Time you all got some much-needed rest."
    new "I think the celebrations have come to an end. Time you all got some much-needed rest."

    old "The soldiers offered up some slurred protest, but most were by now so exhausted they welcomed an excuse to put an end to their partying."
    new "The soldiers offered up some slurred protest, but most were by now so exhausted they welcomed an excuse to put an end to their partying."

    old "Only Thomas remained, still laying across the steps. A bottle of wine dangling in his loose grip."
    new "Only Thomas remained, still laying across the steps. A bottle of wine dangling in his loose grip."

    old "Enjoying yourself, I see?"
    new "Enjoying yourself, I see?"

    old "Thomas chortled."
    new "Thomas chortled."

    old "It was quite something, Sis, I'll tell you that."
    new "It was quite something, Sis, I'll tell you that."

    old "I hadn't even noticed it was already day again."
    new "I hadn't even noticed it was already day again."

    old "I think you'd probably do well to get some rest. Your head is going to feel like it's splitting open soon enough."
    new "I think you'd probably do well to get some rest. Your head is going to feel like it's splitting open soon enough."

    old "Thomas laughed."
    new "Thomas laughed."

    old "Or maybe that means I should just carry on, skip all the headache."
    new "Or maybe that means I should just carry on, skip all the headache."

    old "Sarah crossed her arms."
    new "Sarah crossed her arms."

    old "You might be king, but you're also my little brother, and unlike those sycophants, you can trust me to tell you what you actually need, not just what you want to hear."
    new "You might be king, but you're also my little brother, and unlike those sycophants, you can trust me to tell you what you actually need, not just what you want to hear."

    old "And you need to rest."
    new "And you need to rest."

    old "Thomas gave a drunkard's nod."
    new "Thomas gave a drunkard's nod."

    old "You're right, you're right. Just give me a moment."
    new "You're right, you're right. Just give me a moment."

    old "Sarah sat down on the stairs next to Thomas. She put one hand on his shoulder."
    new "Sarah sat down on the stairs next to Thomas. She put one hand on his shoulder."

    old "You know, Thomas, you were very brave yesterday. But if you ever want to talk to me about that day, I mean, really talk, you know you can right?"
    new "You know, Thomas, you were very brave yesterday. But if you ever want to talk to me about that day, I mean, really talk, you know you can right?"

    old "Thomas sat up."
    new "Thomas sat up."

    old "It was incredible, Sarah, absolutely incredible."
    new "It was incredible, Sarah, absolutely incredible."

    old "I've never felt anything like it in my life."
    new "I've never felt anything like it in my life."

    old "To meet them in battle, see these people who want nothing more than to kill you, and to fight, knowing your life depends on it."
    new "To meet them in battle, see these people who want nothing more than to kill you, and to fight, knowing your life depends on it."

    old "It was exhilarating."
    new "It was exhilarating."

    old "Ooh, and when we turned the tide and started to rout them, wow, I can't put it into words."
    new "Ooh, and when we turned the tide and started to rout them, wow, I can't put it into words."

    old "Sarah listened to her brother speak. It was clear that he was being honest."
    new "Sarah listened to her brother speak. It was clear that he was being honest."

    old "She was glad to hear that the battle did not trouble him, but she hadn't expected to see him seemingly enjoying it."
    new "She was glad to hear that the battle did not trouble him, but she hadn't expected to see him seemingly enjoying it."

    old "Well, I'm glad to see you're carrying it well, Thomas."
    new "Well, I'm glad to see you're carrying it well, Thomas."

    old "You're right. I can play tough, and I think I carried myself well, but inside..."
    new "You're right. I can play tough, and I think I carried myself well, but inside..."

    old "Sarah...I try to put on this front of the perfect king. Even on the battlefield, I cover up my fears."
    new "Sarah...I try to put on this front of the perfect king. Even on the battlefield, I cover up my fears."

    old "But all around me, I saw the faces of soldiers, and you could see it in their eyes: they were hungry for the killing."
    new "But all around me, I saw the faces of soldiers, and you could see it in their eyes: they were hungry for the killing."

    old "Thomas paused."
    new "Thomas paused."

    old "I'm not sure I can be like that. Not really, you know, on the inside?"
    new "I'm not sure I can be like that. Not really, you know, on the inside?"

    old "Sarah patted her brother's shoulder to comfort him."
    new "Sarah patted her brother's shoulder to comfort him."

    old "I think that's a good thing, Thomas."
    new "I think that's a good thing, Thomas."

    old "You don't want to be the kind of man that loves bloodshed."
    new "You don't want to be the kind of man that loves bloodshed."

    old "War is a necessity, but only when our enemies leave us no other option."
    new "War is a necessity, but only when our enemies leave us no other option."

    old "Sarah stood up and stuck out her hand to Thomas."
    new "Sarah stood up and stuck out her hand to Thomas."

    old "Taking his sister's hand, Thomas slowly wobbled his way onto his feet."
    new "Taking his sister's hand, Thomas slowly wobbled his way onto his feet."

    old "The bottle slid from his already loose grip and began tumbling down the stairs, rolling off into the hall."
    new "The bottle slid from his already loose grip and began tumbling down the stairs, rolling off into the hall."

    old "Ugh, I really am worse off than I thought."
    new "Ugh, I really am worse off than I thought."

    old "I'll trust you can make it back to your room by yourself, or do I need to get one of the servants to carry you?"
    new "I'll trust you can make it back to your room by yourself, or do I need to get one of the servants to carry you?"

    old "Either I'll make it, or you'll find my asleep somewhere in the hallways. Either way, I'll get some rest."
    new "Either I'll make it, or you'll find my asleep somewhere in the hallways. Either way, I'll get some rest."

    old "Sarah watched her brother stumble away. He had joked, but she was only half sure that she wouldn't actually find him off in some hallway."
    new "Sarah watched her brother stumble away. He had joked, but she was only half sure that she wouldn't actually find him off in some hallway."

    old "Still, she was glad to find him doing well."
    new "Still, she was glad to find him doing well."

    old "The battle had taken a lot out of him, but they had pushed out the invaders."
    new "The battle had taken a lot out of him, but they had pushed out the invaders."

    old "Rosanna was safe, for now."
    new "Rosanna was safe, for now."

    old "Sarah decided to set out for the library to take care of her council duties, but she had only just made it out of the great hall before she saw a familiar face."
    new "Sarah decided to set out for the library to take care of her council duties, but she had only just made it out of the great hall before she saw a familiar face."

    old "Varga was leaning against a wall, reading a map of some sort. His face was very stern when he was focused, and he was too focused to notice Sarah coming upon him."
    new "Varga was leaning against a wall, reading a map of some sort. His face was very stern when he was focused, and he was too focused to notice Sarah coming upon him."

    old "She stuck her hand out, between Varga and the map."
    new "She stuck her hand out, between Varga and the map."

    old "Startled, his face turned from serious to surprised, only to turn happy when he realized it was Sarah."
    new "Startled, his face turned from serious to surprised, only to turn happy when he realized it was Sarah."

    old "You almost gave me a heart attack."
    new "You almost gave me a heart attack."

    old "A heart attack? Didn't know you had so many enemies in the castle to be fearful of."
    new "A heart attack? Didn't know you had so many enemies in the castle to be fearful of."

    old "Just one in particular that's always trying to get me in trouble."
    new "Just one in particular that's always trying to get me in trouble."

    old "Varga looked at her intently."
    new "Varga looked at her intently."

    old "Is that so? Any plans on how you're going to deal with this dangerous enemy?"
    new "Is that so? Any plans on how you're going to deal with this dangerous enemy?"

    old "A few."
    new "A few."

    old "So mysterious."
    new "So mysterious."

    old "Varga folded up his map."
    new "Varga folded up his map."

    old "Anything I can help you with, Sarah?"
    new "Anything I can help you with, Sarah?"

    old "Sarah shook her head and spun around on the back of her heels."
    new "Sarah shook her head and spun around on the back of her heels."

    old "I was going to take care of some work, but now I've found myself distracted by you."
    new "I was going to take care of some work, but now I've found myself distracted by you."

    old "Sarah waved her finger at Varga."
    new "Sarah waved her finger at Varga."

    old "Keeping me from my royal duties, it's treasonous really."
    new "Keeping me from my royal duties, it's treasonous really."

    old "Don't let me get in the way, go right ahead. The library is off that way, but I imagine you know your way around the castle."
    new "Don't let me get in the way, go right ahead. The library is off that way, but I imagine you know your way around the castle."

    old "Sarah sighed."
    new "Sarah sighed."

    old "Ugh, you're no fun."
    new "Ugh, you're no fun."

    old "Varga chuckled."
    new "Varga chuckled."

    old "You seemed to think otherwise last night."
    new "You seemed to think otherwise last night."

    old "Sarah looked around, making sure they were alone."
    new "Sarah looked around, making sure they were alone."

    old "Maybe that was just clouded judgement from the alcohol."
    new "Maybe that was just clouded judgement from the alcohol."

    old "Varga suddenly grabs Sarah by the waist, spins her around and pins her with her back against the wall."
    new "Varga suddenly grabs Sarah by the waist, spins her around and pins her with her back against the wall."

    old "He pauses for a moment."
    new "He pauses for a moment."

    old "Sarah parts her lips, encouraging him on."
    new "Sarah parts her lips, encouraging him on."

    old "Varga leans in, pressing his lips against hers."
    new "Varga leans in, pressing his lips against hers."

    old "Sarah feels him pinning her body against the wall as his tongue slides into her mouth."
    new "Sarah feels him pinning her body against the wall as his tongue slides into her mouth."

    old "She eagerly meets his with hers."
    new "She eagerly meets his with hers."

    old "For a moment his hands explore her body over her dress, but then she finds him suddenly backing off."
    new "For a moment his hands explore her body over her dress, but then she finds him suddenly backing off."

    old "Sarah reaches with her mouth, desperately trying to get him back on her."
    new "Sarah reaches with her mouth, desperately trying to get him back on her."

    old "She only finds Varga smiling back at her, still holding her up against the wall."
    new "She only finds Varga smiling back at her, still holding her up against the wall."

    old "So, what's your excuse now?"
    new "So, what's your excuse now?"

    old "Sarah knew she had none, nor would she offer any if she had. She wanted him to take her right now if they could get away with it."
    new "Sarah knew she had none, nor would she offer any if she had. She wanted him to take her right now if they could get away with it."

    old "But the castle was full of wandering servants, always watching, listening, gossiping."
    new "But the castle was full of wandering servants, always watching, listening, gossiping."

    old "She felt her unsatisfied lust make way for frustation."
    new "She felt her unsatisfied lust make way for frustation."

    old "So proud of yourself."
    new "So proud of yourself."

    old "Sarah pushed Varga aside and stepped back into the middle of the hallway."
    new "Sarah pushed Varga aside and stepped back into the middle of the hallway."

    old "You're angry?"
    new "You're angry?"

    old "I just...I wish we could be together, really together."
    new "I just...I wish we could be together, really together."

    old "Varga took her hand."
    new "Varga took her hand."

    old "I know, Sarah. But out here...we need to be careful."
    new "I know, Sarah. But out here...we need to be careful."

    old "Sarah pulled her hand away and began to walk towards the library."
    new "Sarah pulled her hand away and began to walk towards the library."

    old "She mumbled to herself in frustration."
    new "She mumbled to herself in frustration."

    old "Always so damn careful."
    new "Always so damn careful."

    old "Sarah set out for the library to take care of the day's duties."
    new "Sarah set out for the library to take care of the day's duties."

